The paper deals with optimization problems related to facility location, which is a classic topic in computer science. The use of approximation algorithms suggests that the paper belongs to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) category. The problem formulation and the use of graph theory and optimization techniques suggest that the paper could also belong to the cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.RO (Robotics) categories. Finally, the paper's focus on optimization and approximation suggests that it could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category.
